# Binnacle

In this document I'm going to reorder the writing structure for my thesis project. My main study object is justification of violence, and my main argument is that sense of justice about de distribution of recourses in the country has the effect of incresing justifications of violence for social change, and decreasing justifications of violence for social control. In a more simple way, I'm proposing that people feels more injustices and that has an effect on his view about the uses of violence.

As you can see, my main subject proyect and my main argument is set, but I'm having troubles in telling the story. The first semester of my project I focussed a lot in reviewing literature about the concept **violence** and **justification of violence**. I spend almost all the semester closed only to that two concepts, having the following effects:

- I read a lot about violence, so I manage the subject. That's good.
- Almost all the paper I read was from philosophical and theorical perspectives. That's good in one point of view, because it allows me to have a deep understanding of the debate about justifications of violence. Nevertheless, it also was bad because I focussed too much in that subjects, and my thesis is (1) from a sociological perspective and (2) empirical, not a theorical one.
- It gived me a short time of the semester for read about the empirical literature about justifications of violence.
- I closed too much to the concept of justificacion of violence, and I left apart other related concepts.

This second semester I has been less motivated and with less energy. That implies that I'm working in short and intense periods, especially when I had some deadline. For the first deadline I re-wrote the intro and the conceptual and empirical antecedents. That implies re-reading my empirical literature with a fine grain eye. That's good. I achieved denoting the theories used in the study of justifications of violence and it's cronology. Nevertheless, my thesis professor guide tell my that I have to re-write my intro and my conceptual antecedents. I have to tell the story in another way, that's why I'm writing this document.

So, I'm going to put the two writing structures that I have used until now and I'm going to elaborate a new one. The main goal is that the audience find the meaning in my proposal.

Let's go.

